<p>Well. This fits into my headcanon quite interestingly&#8230;</p>
<p>In particular, the actual mental state of a reality bender might actually be inherently delusional depending their surroundings. A reality bender would prefer low hume environments because they experience hume levels inversely to people with normal hume levels.</p>
<p>&#8230;this makes low-hume entities seek high-hume areas, and high-hume entities seek low-hume areas, making the overall hume levels in balance.</p>
<p>&#8230;so what happens when everyone and every area is of equal hume balance? <em><strong>Hume entropy, anyone?</strong></em></p>

