			<div class="content" id="post-content-2283709">
									

<p>Sorry if this counts as necroposting, but seeing your analogy, I realized something. When my mom makes bread, she often puts flour on her hands. This way, the dough won't stick to her hands as much. In this way, reality benders can be considered as people with more flour on their hands, unbound by the stickiness of reality. They can mold it and shape it into the bread they want, and add what spices and ingredients they feel are appropriate without being bound. People with less humes are stuck to the dough, and are affected by it more. If local reality is bent, then the people can be bent easier along with reality. Your analogy is way, way better than you think. Good job.</p>

